What Is It ?
============
Package kz, named after its creator, Karel Zimmer, contains scripts for
installing and managing Debian and Debian-based systems such as Ubuntu.

Also installs (dependencies)
============================
dialog          - Displays user-friendly dialog boxes from shell scripts (TUI)
pkexec          - Run commands as another user with polkit authorization
polkitd         - Framework for managing administrative policies and privileges
psmisc          - Utilities that use the proc file system (e.g. fuser)
python3         - Interactive high-level object-oriented language
rsync           - Fast, versatile, remote (and local) file-copying tool
xdg-user-dirs   - Tool to manage well known user directories
zenity          - Display graphical dialog boxes from shell scripts (GUI)

How To Use
==========
For how to use this package see Checklist installation.
Checklist installation can be found on the site https://karelzimmer.nl/en,
under Linux.

